parameters:
\N<Rozaro>Are you referring to the injury to my right eye...? Thanks
to your protection, it wasn't fatal. But I might not recover
my vision.
\N<Rozaro>What about you...? How's the child in your belly?

\N<Rozaro>I see... that's good. It's a small piece of good fortune
amidst the misfortune.

\N<Segi>Um... more importantly, why? I heard you didn't join the
Ludan forces and chose to stay in this town instead.

\N<Rozaro>Ah... I've had a lot to think about after this incident.
I've grown thoroughly sick of the Ludan lot. Of course, that
includes myself for having been part of such an organization
for so long.

\N<Rozaro>But... that might just be an excuse. The real reason might
be because there's a kind and pure woman like you in this
town... perhaps.
\N<Rozaro>Ah, don't misunderstand me. I mean no ulterior motive.

\N<Rozaro>Being touched by a woman like you made me sick of a world
filled with slaughter and deceit like Ludan's... that's all
there is to it.

\N<Rozaro>That said, every time you look at me, you're probably
reminded of those days. It's all due to my inadequacy... at
least let me make amends.

\N<Rozaro>And... let's swear never to speak of that time to anyone for
as long as we live.

\N<Rozaro>Also... what Tseda and the others said at that time was
true.

\N<Rozaro>I was... while being part of Ludan, I never once indulged in
the beastly acts they did.

\N<Rozaro>It's true. I thought giving in to desires was a sign of
immaturity and above all, I believed it had nothing to do
with my own growth.

\N<Rozaro>In that sense... it was good that my first time was with a
woman like you. Even if it was a terrible misfortune for
you.

\N<Segi>I will pretend I didn't hear what you just said. So please,
never say such things again.

\N<Rozaro>...I see. I don't understand why, but if that's what you
wish, I'll comply.
\N<Rozaro>It seems I've been with Ludan for far too long.

\N<Rozaro>Believe me. I want to change. If there are any shortcomings
in me from now on, please point them out without hesitation.

\N<Yuia>You... what are you doing here. A former Ludan soldier,
right? What do you want with my wife?

\N<Rozaro>I swear I haven't done anything. But I won't make excuses.
Everything that happened to this town and your wife... it's
all my fault, due to my inadequacy.

\N<Segi>Indeed, this man is a former Ludan soldier...! But nothing
has happened! So please...!

\N<Yuia>Even if nothing happened to you, think about what those
Ludan soldiers did to this town... and what they did to us
in the past!

\N<Yuia>Considering that, there's no way I can forgive them...!
There's no way I can forgive them!!

\N<Yuia>Just because you've left the army and apologized doesn't
mean everything is forgotten! If resentment could disappear
so easily, we would never have hated them in the first
place!

\N<Yuia>They are... supposed to be that kind of existence to both
you and me, aren't they!?
\N<Segi>You're absolutely right. Of course, I too...

\N<Segi>But... even so, I don't want to see Lord Yuia hurt an
unarmed person who is not showing any hostility towards us.
\N<Segi>Even if it's for the sake of me and the baby in my belly.

\N<Segi>But to be honest... I just want to forget. Maybe I just
don't want it to be brought up again.

\N<Segi>Besides... I don't want to celebrate the birth of this child
with bloodstained hands.

\N<Rozaro>I'm deeply sorry once again. I don't expect everything to be
forgiven just by bowing my head in submission, but
apologizing from the bottom of my heart is the only way I
know how.

\N<Rozaro>So at least... let me dedicate the rest of my life to you
two, and to the baby that will be born.

It was incredibly difficult to properly impose on one's
heart what to forgive and what to hate.

At that time, I might have been simply swayed by the words
and actions of others, in a sense.

Lord Yuia, who took my words to heart and tried to melt away
the hatred within him.

And Rozaro-san, who regretted the past and expressed a
desire to change.

Yes, at that time, I was just watching the determination and
actions of others... in reality, I hadn't gained anything
myself.
I was such a terribly diminutive being.
